{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"grassgreen-clotty-duck","description":"# purge-bridge commits on the tickets tracker with a raw, unlocked whole-index git commit (same class as the enrich-queue prune race)\n\n## Summary\n\n`rebar/_commands/purge_bridge.py` (~lines 135-152) commits its ticket-directory deletions with a\nraw `git -C <tracker> add -A` + `git -C <tracker> commit --no-verify` that takes **neither the\nunified store write lock nor a commit pathspec** — the same defect class as bug\n`eclectic-spotted-barb` (the enrich-queue prune), where an unlocked whole-index commit races\nconcurrent locked store writes and sweeps/strands them.\n\nDiscovered during the Step-7 sibling sweep for `eclectic-spotted-barb`. Lower exposure than the\nenrich-queue prune (which fired opportunistically on every write via the `[agents]` drain child):\n`purge-bridge` is a **manual operator command**, so it only races if an operator runs it while\nagents are writing. Filed separately because (a) its blast radius is much smaller and (b) the fix\nis not a drop-in `delete_events` swap — it removes whole ticket **directories** via `git add -A`,\nso it needs the unified write lock wrapped around a pathspec-scoped or `-A` commit (or a locked\nbatch delete), not the enrich-queue prune's exact pattern.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. While concurrent agents are performing normal locked store writes, run `rebar purge-bridge`.\n2. Its unlocked `git add -A` + whole-index `git commit` can sweep a concurrent writer's staged\n   event into the purge commit / advance HEAD under the writer's ref update, dropping/stranding\n   that write (same sweep-and-strand as `eclectic-spotted-barb`).\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n\n- **Expected:** every store write serializes through the unified write lock (invariant I5); a\n  concurrent write is never dropped by a maintenance command's commit.\n- **Actual:** `purge-bridge`'s commit runs outside the lock and can race concurrent locked writes.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `purge_bridge.py`'s deletion commit routes through the unified store write lock (no raw\n  unlocked `git add -A` + `git commit` on the tracker).\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'subprocess.run.*git.*commit' src/rebar/_commands/purge_bridge.py` shows no\n    unlocked whole-index commit; the write path acquires the store write lock.\n- [ ] A concurrency regression test (mirroring\n  `tests/interfaces/store/test_enrich_drain_prune_concurrency.py`) shows `purge-bridge` racing\n  concurrent locked writes loses nothing (RED before, GREEN after).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"4dd2-312b-7ded-4938","parent_id":"","priority":3,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"purge-bridge commits on the tickets tracker with a raw, unlocked whole-index git commit (same class as the enrich-queue prune race)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784240879462290001,"uuid":"84cc9fb2-ed42-4c9a-a25f-870c4de9595f"}